summary: This document appears to be a legal text related to the Articles of Incorporation for a corporation, detailing indemnification provisions for directors and officers. It outlines the rights of individuals involved in legal actions related to their corporate roles and the corporation's ability to amend its Articles. The document is marked as confidential.
keyFacts: The document discusses indemnification for directors and officers of the corporation.
It states that individuals involved in legal actions related to their corporate roles may be indemnified against costs and expenses.
The corporation reserves the right to amend its Articles of Incorporation.
It is marked as confidential under Federal Rule of Criminal Procedure 6(e).
